### Task Management API Tests

### 1. Create a new task
POST http://localhost:8080/api/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Prepare monthly report",
  "description": "Create financial report for March"
}

### 2. Create task with validation error (title too short)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "ab",
  "description": "This should fail validation"
}

### 3. Get all tasks (first page)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tasks?page=0&size=10

### 4. Get tasks filtered by status
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tasks?page=0&size=10&status=NEW

### 5. Get task by ID
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tasks/1

### 6. Get non-existent task (should return 404)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tasks/999

### 7. Update task status
PATCH http://localhost:8080/api/tasks/1/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "IN_PROGRESS"
}

### 8. Update non-existent task status (should return 404)
PATCH http://localhost:8080/api/tasks/999/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "DONE"
}

### 9. Delete task
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/tasks/1

### 10. Delete non-existent task (should return 404)
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/tasks/999